00078 const string version = "$Revision$";
00079 const string prompt = "gse-test: ";
00080 const string options = "sS:p:dv";
00081 const string usage = "gse-test [-s [-S string] -d -v [-p dds file]\n\
00082 Test the grid selections expression evaluation software.\n\
00083 Options:\n\
00084     -s: Feed the input stream directly into the expression scanner, does\n\
00085         not parse.\n\
00086         -S: <string> Scan the string as if it was standard input.\n\
00087         -p: <dds file> parse stdin using the grid defined in the DDS file.\n\
00088     -d: Turn on expression parser debugging.\n\
00089         -v: Print the version of expr-test";

00091 int
00092 main(int argc, char *argv[])
00093 {
00094     GetOpt getopt(argc, argv, options.c_str());
00095     int option_char;
00096     bool scan_gse = false, scan_gse_string = false;
00097     bool test_parse = false;
00098     string constraint = "";
00099     string dds_file;
00100     // process options
00101 
00102     while ((option_char = getopt()) != EOF)
00103     switch (option_char) {
00104       case 'd': 
00105         gse_debug = true;
00106         break;
00107       case 's':
00108         scan_gse = true;
00109         break;
00110       case 'S':
00111         scan_gse_string = true;
00112         scan_gse = true;
00113         constraint = getopt.optarg;
00114         break;
00115       case 'p':
00116         test_parse = true;
00117         dds_file = getopt.optarg;
00118         break;
00119       case 'v':
00120         fprintf( stderr, "%s: %s\n", argv[0], version.c_str() ) ;
00121         exit(0);
00122       case '?': 
00123       default:
00124         fprintf( stderr, "%s\n", usage.c_str() ) ;
00125         exit(1);
00126         break;
00127     }
00128 
00129     if (!scan_gse && !test_parse) {
00130     fprintf( stderr, "%s\n", usage.c_str() ) ;
00131     exit(1);
00132     }
00133 
00134     // run selected tests
00135 
00136     if (scan_gse) {
00137     if (scan_gse_string)
00138         test_gse_scanner(constraint.c_str());
00139     else
00140         test_gse_scanner(true);
00141     exit(0);
00142     }
00143 
00144     if (test_parse) {
00145     test_parser(dds_file);
00146     exit(0);
00147     }
00148 }

00152 void
00153 test_gse_scanner(const char *str)
00154 {
00155     gse_restart(0);
00156     void *buffer = gse_string(str);
00157     gse_switch_to_buffer(buffer);
00158 
00159     test_gse_scanner(false);
00160 
00161     gse_delete_buffer(buffer);
00162 }

00164 void
00165 test_gse_scanner(bool show_prompt)
00166 {
00167     if (show_prompt) 
00168     fprintf( stdout, "%s", prompt.c_str() ) ;// first prompt
00169 
00170     int tok;
00171     while ((tok = gse_lex())) {
00172     switch (tok) {
00173       case SCAN_WORD:
00174         fprintf( stdout, "WORD: %s\n", gse_lval.id ) ;
00175         break;
00176       case SCAN_INT:
00177         fprintf( stdout, "INT: %d\n", (int)gse_lval.val ) ;
00178         break;
00179       case SCAN_FLOAT:
00180         fprintf( stdout, "FLOAT: %f\n", gse_lval.val ) ;
00181         break;
00182       case SCAN_EQUAL:
00183         fprintf( stdout, "EQUAL: %d\n", gse_lval.op ) ;
00184         break;
00185       case SCAN_NOT_EQUAL:
00186         fprintf( stdout, "NOT_EQUAL: %d\n", gse_lval.op ) ;
00187         break;
00188       case SCAN_GREATER:
00189         fprintf( stdout, "GREATER: %d\n", gse_lval.op ) ;
00190         break;
00191       case SCAN_GREATER_EQL:
00192         fprintf( stdout, "GREATER_EQL: %d\n", gse_lval.op ) ;
00193         break;
00194       case SCAN_LESS:
00195         fprintf( stdout, "LESS: %d\n", gse_lval.op ) ;
00196         break;
00197       case SCAN_LESS_EQL:
00198         fprintf( stdout, "LESS_EQL: %d\n", gse_lval.op ) ;
00199         break;
00200       default:
00201         fprintf( stdout, "Error: Unrecognized input\n" ) ;
00202     }
00203     fprintf( stdout, "%s", prompt.c_str() ) ; // print prompt after output
00204     }
00205 }

00207 // Create and return a map vector for use in testing the GSE parser. The map
00208 // is monotonically increasing in T.
00209 
00210 template<class T>
00211 static T*
00212 new_map(int size)
00213 {
00214     T *t = new T[size];
00215     srand(time(0));
00216     double offset = rand()/(double)((1<<15)-1);
00217     double space = rand()/(double)((1<<15)-1);
00218 
00219     offset *= 10.0;
00220     space *= 10.0;
00221 
00222     for (int i = 0; i < size; ++i)
00223     t[i] = (int)(i * space  + offset);
00224 
00225     return t;
00226 }

00228 void
00229 test_parser(const string &dds_file)
00230 {
00231     // Read the grid
00232 
00233     Grid *grid = 0;
00234     DDS dds;
00235     dds.parse(dds_file);
00236     for (DDS::Vars_iter p = dds.var_begin(); p != dds.var_end(); p++)
00237     {
00238     if ((*p)->type() == dods_grid_c)
00239         grid = dynamic_cast<Grid *>((*p));
00240     }
00241     if (!grid) {
00242     fprintf( stderr,
00243          "Could not find a grid variable in the DDS, exiting.\n" ) ; 
00244     exit(1);
00245     }
00246     
00247     // Load the grid map indices. The GSEClause object does not process the
00248     // Array values, but does need valid map data. Assume that the maps are
00249     // all either Float64 or Int32 maps.
00250 
00251     for (Grid::Map_iter p = grid->map_begin(); p != grid->map_end(); p++)
00252     {
00253     Array *map = dynamic_cast<Array *>((*p));
00254     // Can safely assume that maps are one-dimensional Arrays.
00255     Array::Dim_iter diter = map->dim_begin() ;
00256     int size = map->dimension_size(diter);
00257     switch(map->var()->type()) {
00258       case dods_int16_c: {
00259         dods_int16 *vec = new_map<dods_int16>(size);
00260         map->val2buf(vec);
00261         break;
00262       }
00263       case dods_int32_c: {
00264         dods_int32 *vec = new_map<dods_int32>(size);
00265         map->val2buf(vec);
00266         break;
00267       }
00268       case dods_float32_c: {
00269         dods_float32 *vec = new_map<dods_float32>(size);
00270         map->val2buf(vec);
00271         break;
00272       }
00273       case dods_float64_c: {
00274         dods_float64 *vec = new_map<dods_float64>(size);
00275         map->val2buf(vec);
00276         break;
00277       }
00278       default:
00279         fprintf( stderr, "Invalid map vector type in grid, exiting.\n" ) ;
00280         exit(1);
00281     }
00282     }
00283 
00284     dds.print(stdout);
00285     for (Grid::Map_iter p = grid->map_begin(); p != grid->map_end(); p++)
00286     (*p)->print_val(stdout);
00287 
00288     // Parse the GSE and mark the selection in the Grid.
00289 
00290     gse_restart(stdin);
00291 
00292     fprintf( stdout, "%s", prompt.c_str() ) ;
00293     fflush( stdout ) ;
00294     
00295     gse_arg *arg = new gse_arg(grid);
00296     bool status = false ;
00297     try {
00298     status = gse_parse((void *)arg) == 0;
00299     }
00300     catch (Error &e) {
00301     e.display_message();
00302     exit(1);
00303     }
00304 
00305     if (status) {
00306     fprintf( stdout, "Input parsed\n" ) ;
00307     GSEClause *gsec = arg->get_gsec();
00308     fprintf( stdout, "Start: %d Stop: %d\n", gsec->get_start(),
00309                          gsec->get_stop() ) ;
00310     }
00311     else
00312     fprintf( stdout, "Input did not parse\n" ) ;
00313 }
